"title": "5343: idleness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5343",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Laziness or unproductiveness. As work is hallowed by God's working, idleness is regarded as a sin against oneself and society.</p>\n<h2>Idleness reproached</h2>\n<h3>In terms of daily labour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:14\">1TH 5:14</a></strong> <em>Paul to the Christians at Thessalonica.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:24\">PRO 19:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:4\">PRO 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:13\">PRO 22:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:13-Prov26:16\">PRO 26:13–26:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:6-2Thess3:15\">2TH 3:6–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:13\">1TI 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:12\">TIT 1:12</a></p>\n<h3>In matters of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:11-Heb6:12\">HEB 6:11–6:12</a></strong> <em>To Christians who were tempted to give up.</em></p>\n<h2>Idleness discouraged by examples of industriousness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:6-Prov6:8\">PRO 6:6–6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:27\">PRO 31:27</a> <em>the good wife</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:6\">ECC 11:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:7-2Thess3:9\">2TH 3:7–3:9</a> <em>Paul referring to his practice of not depending on others for his living</em></p>\n<h2>The results of idleness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:9-Prov6:11\">PRO 6:9–6:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:26\">PRO 10:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:24\">PRO 12:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:4\">PRO 13:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:19\">PRO 15:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:15\">PRO 19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:4\">PRO 20:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:18\">ECC 10:18</a></p>",
